vertheless continued his work to point out the impact of war, genocide and displacement on children, who were often forgotten in major discussions about the war and the losses it had created. This volume provides a short biographical outline of Papanek and a theoretical discussion about the impact of war and genocide on children who are forced out of their lives and who were not only physically displaced as a consequence. The second part of the book assembles some of Papanek's important texts about the children he had worked with and for, to make his thoughts and important considerations accessible for a broader academic and non-academic public alike.  afunded by Nord University  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4a2. Weltkrieg. 4aErnst Papanek. 4aFlucht. 4aHolocaust. 7aHISTORY / Modern / General.2bisacsh  aErnst Papanek, Holocaust, World War II, Refuge.2 aNord Universityefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2021z978311075072008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1z97831107507060 cEPUBz97831106795020 cprintz978311067931140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110679410zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110679410zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110679410/original  a978-3-11-075070-6 DG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1b2021  a978-3-11-075072-0 DG Ebook Package English 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA